The paper focuses on detecting and generating domains for malware families, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also utilizes deep learning techniques, specifically generative adversarial networks, which suggests that it may fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper addresses challenges in training the GAN, which may fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
